Package com.example.popsicle.models

Class Universe

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.popsicle.models.Universe
  • public class Universe
extends java.lang.Object
    Universe handles all the actions that are going on in the game. It also creates the "Universe" by creating the elements/models in the game, such as the Popsicles/Candies, Characters, Clouds, Console, and the Syrups.

      • CharacterMove

        public void CharacterMove​(Position pos,
                          Character character)
        The CharacterMove function is called in the MoveCharacterAction class, that will be executed when the user touches the screen. This function will check whether the user touches the screen on the coordinates/location of the Up, Left, Down, or Right console button. It will then set the Boolean isMovingUp/Left/Down/Right to true depending on the Console that is clicked.
        Parameters:
        pos - position of the Console in the Universe (in this case, the user's touch on screen)
        character - the Character class that we want to move (character A or B)

      • addSyrup

        public void addSyrup​(float x,
                     float y,
                     java.lang.String direction)
        The addSyrup method is to add the Syrup into the game or the Universe. The syrup will be automatically shot by the Clouds A1, A2, B1, or B2 when the game is started. This method is called in the MainController when the Thread is being run. The syrups are added to the universe at a random time and at a random direction every time. This serves as an obstacle in the game.
        Parameters:
        x - the x-coordinate of the Syrup position
        y - the y-coordinate of the Syrup position
        direction - from which Cloud is the Syrup coming from (either "a1", "a2", "b1", or "b2")

      • syrupSteps

        public void syrupSteps()
        The syrupSteps method is to make all the Syrups in the Universe move in a certain direction, depending on from which Clouds is the Syrups being shot from

      • checkSyrupCollisionA

        public void checkSyrupCollisionA()
        The checkSyrupCollisionA method is to check if any of the Syrups in the Universe collides with either Character A. If it collides with the Character, then the game will be terminated with Character B winning and Character A loosing.

      • checkSyrupCollisionB

        public void checkSyrupCollisionB()
        The checkSyrupCollisionB method is to check if any of the Syrups in the Universe collides with either Character B. If it collides with the Character, then the game will be terminated with Character A winning and Character B loosing.

      • checkPopsicleACollision

        public void checkPopsicleACollision()
        The checkPopsicleACollision method is to check if Character A is in close enough proximity to the popsicle of Character B. If it is the game will be terminated with Character A winning and Character B loosing.

      • checkPopsicleBCollision

        public void checkPopsicleBCollision()
        The checkPopsicleBCollision method is to check if Character B is in close enough proximity to the popsicle of Character A. If it is the game will be terminated with Character B winning and Character A loosing.

      • randomlyAddSyrups

        public void randomlyAddSyrups​(int n,
                              Clouds cloud,
                              java.lang.String direction)
        This method is to add syrups in the universe at random direction. This method is called at the main controller.
        Parameters:
        n - The random integer chosen to generate a random direction of the syrup
        cloud - The cloud in which the syrup is shooting from
        direction - The specified cloud (either "a1", "a2", "b1", or "b2")

      • updateCharacter

        public void updateCharacter()
